{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"symbolKind":"class","title":"ScrollLayout","externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScrollLayout"}],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation